WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning. It's Friday, April twenty-fourth, twenty twenty-six. Three things

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
for the day. One: put a date on later with

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Katelyn — last night's conversation ended mutually, not coldly. Two:

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
yesterday's briefing got the Katelyn thread wrong. The retraction is

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
today's lead. And three: reply to Dustin. Five days. Forty-five

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
seconds of typing. Memory correction first. Yesterday's briefing described a

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
ten-fifteen P-M message about the intimate thread, sitting unreplied. No

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
such message exists. The real thread was a fifty-five minute

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
conversation, from eight fifty-two to nine forty-seven P-M, about geography,

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
moving, and the absence of a plan. It ended with

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
her line — I mean yeah but we can talk

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
later. She came back warm — Merlin bird photos at

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
ten thirty-one, six more photos at ten thirty-two, and chatty

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
post-movie texts at one-nineteen A-M. Why it matters: the framing

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
changes the call to action. Not repair first — schedule

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
the follow-up. When she wakes, reply to the Merlin photos

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
first, then put a real time on later. Sunday afternoon

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
works. Iran. Trump posted a shoot-and-kill order overnight for Iranian

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
Revolutionary Guard mine-laying boats in the Strait of Hormuz. Sourced

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
across Al Jazeera, N-B-C, C-B-S, Axios, TIME, Washington Post, and

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
P-B-S. The ceasefire framing is still intact — the extension

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
remains indefinite. But rules of engagement were loosened without calling

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
the ceasefire off. Manifold moved: Hormuz-normal-by-April-thirtieth up three points to

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
eight percent — that's resolution compression, not a re-read. Brent

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
above one-ten by June thirtieth at seventy-nine percent. Iran retaliates

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
against U-S blockade by July first at sixty-eight percent. Anthropic

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
— quieter Friday, noisier backdrop. N-E-C partnership to build Japan's

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
largest A-I engineering workforce, announced Thursday Japan time. Thin on

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
specifics. And Boris Cherny shipped the Claude Code post-mortem —

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
three technical changes compounded. Reasoning-effort change. Verbosity prompt update. Caching

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
bug in version two-point-one-point-one-one-six. All three reverted. Limits reset for

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
everyone on April twentieth. The approval read: public incident detail

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
at infra-vendor standards. The disapproval read from r/ClaudeAI: silent on

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
the invisible context-window instructions surfaced in February's breach coverage. Now

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
the big miss I have to patch. OpenAI shipped G-P-T

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
five-point-five Thursday — codenamed Spud, after the potato emoji OpenAI

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
used to tease it. Went wide to Plus, Pro, Business,

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
and Enterprise. A-P-I access coming very soon. State-of-the-art on fourteen

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
benchmarks versus four for Claude Opus four-point-seven and two for

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Gemini three-point-one Pro — per OpenAI's own comparison. Eighty-two point

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
seven percent on Terminal-Bench two-point-zero, narrowly beating Claude Mythos Preview.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
One million token context. Pricing, when the A-P-I opens: five

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
dollars per million input tokens, thirty dollars per million output

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
— exactly twice G-P-T five-point-four. G-P-T five-point-five Pro at thirty

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
and one-eighty. Why it matters for your Anthropic application thread:

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
this is the single biggest competitive data point this week.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
A new OpenAI flagship six weeks after five-point-four is an

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
acceleration statement, and the benchmark comparison is explicitly against Opus

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
and Gemini. Watch whether Anthropic ships a response inside April.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
DeepSeek V-four — reframed against five-point-five. Largest open-weights model ever.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
V-four Pro at one-point-seven-four and three-point-four-eight per million tokens. V-four

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
Flash at fourteen cents and twenty-eight cents. Now undercutting G-P-T

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
five-point-five at five and thirty — that's a wider gap

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
than yesterday's five-point-four comparison showed. The frontier cost floor story

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
is bigger, not smaller, after yesterday's OpenAI shipment. Simon Willison

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
has the cleanest write-up. The Manifold read on Anthropic-greater-than-OpenAI twenty

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
twenty-six: sixty percent, down four points on two days. Earlier

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
read was the one-T secondary story didn't lift; post-mortem drag.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Revised read: the bigger drag was OpenAI shipping into the

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
window. A competitor headlining a new frontier model the same

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
week a rival publishes an incident report is the pattern

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
